NIGERIAN Singer, Khalil recently premiered his music video Grown from his just released debut extended play(EP). The EP entitled Grown is a seven – track multi facet project that shows Khalil’s creative abilities switching styles and genre effortlessly. The video which was directed by WG is a major project by the ace rapper and profound reggae/dance hall and afro-fusion artiste; who has been in the scene for about 10 years doing music as Ghetto P. Khalil’s transformation and growth is evident in his style, his lyrics and delivery, the entire project is a sweet melodious relaxing feel. The seventh track is a classic rap track with a retrospective message and indigenous hook. It’s a track that identifies with one’s roots. Tracks one to six was produced by Words while track seven was co-produced by Words and Spell.